metadata.name: Breeding Grounds #412
metadata.description:
Social Networks.
Molecular Clouds.
Neuronal Circuitries.
Quantum Mechanical Structures.

Blurring Boundaries.
Infinite Self-Similarities.

Total.
Mess.

Perfect.
Order.

/////
Each element (besides the painting ground textures) is based on the underlying subdivided grid which is sometimes exposed like some kind of preliminary drawing.

Note on the split:
After seeing some of the outputs, Sermin had a dream about ‚ÄúBreeding Grounds‚Äù and I decided to incorporate events and feelings from her dream into the project. That's how the names of the color palettes came about. Thank you for naming them, Sermin!

Press 's' to save a .png with the current resolution (2000x3000).
If you want a file with higher resolution and/or without the ‚ÄúPainting Ground Textures‚Äù for printing please contact me via Twitter or Discord. 

/////
Created with p5.js

Twitter: @serminmin / @pxlshrd

metadata.name: Page33 #46
metadata.description:
Just one more page. 


Default canvas size is 800x1200px. Add &sc=x to the url, where x is any integer, to increase the size of the canvas.

Press "s" to save a png image.

Made with javascript/rust/webassembly

metadata.name: Jubilee #47
metadata.description:
Jubilee is a flow field festival celebrating creation. Ribbons scattered through a space meet one another, overlap, and are generally at the mercy of the forces acting upon them. But collectively, what complex forms can they create?

Canvas size is 1200 x 1600 pixels, in either portrait or landscape.

To change canvas size:

[1] 1200 x 1600 
[2] 2400 x 3200 
[3] 4800 x 6400

[s] will save a png at the chosen resolution.

metadata.name: Future Echoes #368
metadata.description:
Future Echoes is a Generative Art experiment showing how a minute change in initial conditions can give rise to vastly different outcomes.

Created using pure JavaScript, without external libraries.

:: STYLES ::

- Pencil ----------- 68.5%
- Chalk ------------ 16%
- Biro ------------- 8%
- Error ------------ 4%
- Blueprints ------- 2%
- Final Warning ---- 1%
- Neon ------------- 0.5%


:: INSTRUCTIONS ::

- Add ?fullScreen=true to the url to render at full screen size
- To download the image in PNG format, press [s].

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #207
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden ‚Äútemplate‚Äù canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‚Äòtemplate‚Äô image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution
